Several drivers and their passengers have been stranded at Mombasa-Nairobi highway for the past 12 hours.The group has been stuck in a jam stretching from Maungu to Makina following four accidents on the route.The situation has been complicated by the ongoing construction on various sections of the highway.Mohamed Said, a truck driver, said vehicles can't proceed to or leave Mombasa adding that they had not spotted traffic police officers on site."I have been here since 5pm yesterday (Sunday) and I have not moved even an inch," he said, adding that he might not deliver a container to Tororo, Uganda within the deadline.Some drivers opted for the SGR reserve road.The situation has mostly affected women and children who have been stuck in the more than 40 km snarl-up complicated by heavy rains that hit the area on Sunday.